DataElement.preferredName: Biospecimen Whole Cell Pellet Volume Milliliter Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The numerical response indicating the volume of a whole cell sample collected and compacted by centrifugation in a liquid suspension.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Any material sample taken from a biological entity for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes, including a sample obtained from a living organism or taken from the biological object after halting of all its life functions. Biospecimen can contain one or more components including but not limited to cellular molecules, cells, tissues, organs, body fluids, embryos, and body excretory products._Including all components without exception; constituting the full amount or extent or duration; complete._A cell sample collected and compacted by centrifugation of a liquid suspension._The amount of three dimensional space occupied by an object or the capacity of a space or container.

RepresentationTerm.preferredDefinition: Volume; the amount of 3-dimensional space occupied by an object.:A measure of volume for a liquid.  A milliliter is approximately 950 times smaller than a quart and 30 times smaller than a fluid ounce.  A milliliter of liquid and a cubic centimeter (cc) of liquid are the same.:A numerical quantity measured or assigned or computed.
